    it should be on the same level!

o Windows: are the file mapping routines really ok? does the file mapping
    handle have to be created over the whole file size? does it have to be
    created with every mmap call??
    o CreateFileMapping: file size can be 0 (will then use the full file size)
    o get a decent profiler
        o win32: evaluate performance with FILE_FLAG_NO_BUFFERING 
    	o get rid of copy-on-write! but then we also don't need to pwrite()??
    o test with big file sizes on 32bit Windows - does it fail?
        http://support.microsoft.com/kb/177415
    o unix: in read-only files only map for reading, not for writing
    o why is the file size so huge? we do not store blobs (all records are
        < 8 bytes) -> the freelist is never needed!
        --> it's not the freelist; index pages are split very early and
            therefore are not fully occupied

o can we extend the statistic module to find out if a Database is sequential,
    and then decide to have late page splits when inserting keys?
    o clean up inserts and use routines from hamsterdb v2 (split when 
        descending)

. idea for freelist: we do not have to mark ALL pages in the freelist!
    o use RLE storage for free pages (pages always have the same size, and
        their offset is irrelevant)
    o index pages that are in use do not need to be stored in the freelist
    o use bitmap ONLY for blob pages!
    o need lookup mechanism to map a page ID to a freelist page
        o use a dynamic, sorted table
        o for 256 blob-pages we will have to allocate 1 additional freelist page

